WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:02.245
.

00:02.252 --> 00:09.342
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:09.384 --> 00:10.844
the people are represented

00:10.886 --> 00:12.796
by two separate,
yet equally important groups:

00:12.846 --> 00:14.806
the police,
who investigate crime,

00:14.848 --> 00:17.808
and the district attorneys,
who prosecute the offenders.

00:17.851 --> 00:19.691
These are their stories.

00:20.521 --> 00:23.401
[sirens wailing]

00:25.734 --> 00:27.784
- Call you later?

00:27.819 --> 00:29.069
- That’s OK.

00:30.656 --> 00:32.616
It was fun, but...

00:32.658 --> 00:34.158
- [chuckles]

00:42.668 --> 00:43.708
Hey!

00:45.212 --> 00:46.462
Hey, what’s happening?
What’s happening?

00:46.505 --> 00:47.595
What’s going on?

00:47.631 --> 00:48.671
- Someone’s shooting
down there! Leave!

00:48.715 --> 00:51.715
[screaming]

00:51.760 --> 00:55.220
[tense music]

00:55.264 --> 01:02.404
♪

01:08.569 --> 01:11.239
[groaning]

01:19.037 --> 01:21.287
- [screaming]

01:27.254 --> 01:30.134
- Help me.
Someone, please help me!

01:33.051 --> 01:34.431
- Try not to move.

01:34.469 --> 01:35.759
[stammers]
I don’t know.

01:35.804 --> 01:38.854
- [sobbing]

01:38.890 --> 01:40.230
- This should help
with the bleeding.

01:40.267 --> 01:41.727
- Am I gonna die?
- No.

01:41.768 --> 01:43.478
- [screaming]

01:43.520 --> 01:45.360
- Help will be here soon.

01:47.983 --> 01:49.573
Can you tell me what happened?

01:49.610 --> 01:52.360
- This man,
he pointed his gun at people,

01:52.404 --> 01:55.414
and he just kept pulling
the trigger over and over.

01:55.449 --> 01:57.279
It really hurts.
Please help me.

01:57.326 --> 02:00.036
- Hey, over here!

02:00.078 --> 02:01.748
- I got this.

02:01.788 --> 02:04.868
You’re gonna be OK.
I’m applying pressure.

02:04.916 --> 02:06.666
- Hold it right there, sir.
- Whoa!

02:06.710 --> 02:08.500
Oh, right.

02:08.545 --> 02:11.915
Nolan Price,
Manhattan DA’s office.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.045
How many?

02:13.091 --> 02:14.551
- At least seven.

02:14.593 --> 02:16.683
One of them
was just a young kid.

02:16.720 --> 02:23.640
♪

02:34.112 --> 02:37.162
[phone buzzing]

02:42.621 --> 02:43.661
- Jack?

02:45.290 --> 02:47.080
No, I’m here.

02:47.125 --> 02:49.245
[stammers]
I’m here already.

02:52.005 --> 02:54.585
It’s a nightmare.

02:54.633 --> 02:56.843
It’s an absolute nightmare.

02:59.721 --> 03:03.641
[dramatic music]

03:03.684 --> 03:10.194
♪

03:46.184 --> 03:48.394
It looks like a hate crime.

03:48.437 --> 03:50.477
According to the ME,

03:50.522 --> 03:55.032
all seven DOA appear
to be East or Southeast Asian.

03:55.068 --> 03:56.488
- And the injured?

03:56.528 --> 03:58.528
- I’m not sure.
Numbers are still coming in.

03:58.572 --> 04:01.162
There’s at least--
11 are critical.

04:01.199 --> 04:05.369
But yeah, from what I’m told,
most of them are Asian.

04:05.412 --> 04:06.872
- So all the shell casings
were 9-millimeter,

04:06.913 --> 04:09.123
so I’m guessing
the shooter was using a TEC-9.

04:09.166 --> 04:11.036
- Anyone get a look at the guy?
- Not a good look.

04:11.084 --> 04:13.384
He was wearing a mask,
but multiple witnesses said

04:13.420 --> 04:14.960
that he was short,
medium build,

04:15.005 --> 04:16.715
white male,
wearing a baseball cap,

04:16.757 --> 04:18.927
and had a camouflage gym bag
with him.

04:18.967 --> 04:22.507
- Did they see a label
or any brand in particular?

04:22.554 --> 04:25.184
- No, but they said
one of the straps was broken.

04:25.223 --> 04:26.473
- That’s good.

04:26.516 --> 04:28.476
It gives us something
to work with.

04:28.518 --> 04:31.268
Hopefully,
one of these cameras works.

04:34.900 --> 04:37.990
[screaming]

04:41.406 --> 04:42.616
- Hold it right there.

04:42.657 --> 04:43.657
Zoom in on the bag.

04:47.746 --> 04:50.206
That strap definitely
looks broken to me.

04:50.248 --> 04:52.128
All right, keep rolling.
Let’s see where he goes.

04:52.167 --> 04:54.997
[screaming]

04:58.256 --> 04:59.666
Where the hell is he?

04:59.716 --> 05:01.676
- Not sure.
He didn’t go up the stairs.

05:03.720 --> 05:06.100
- He’s probably
still in the station.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.219
Frank, it’s me.

05:08.266 --> 05:09.766
- Copy.
We’re on it.

05:12.979 --> 05:14.939
Check it out.

05:14.981 --> 05:16.521
That’s blood, but there
were no vics down here.

05:18.652 --> 05:21.452
And there,
that’s a spent shell casing.

05:21.488 --> 05:22.658
Looks like he fired one off

05:22.697 --> 05:23.907
right before he ran
down the tunnel.

05:35.627 --> 05:38.247
- We’re at marker IRT-44.

05:38.296 --> 05:39.956
Have units cover Spring Street.

05:40.006 --> 05:43.836
Have sector cars cover
all emergency exits.

05:46.471 --> 05:48.011
[squeaking]

05:50.725 --> 05:54.395
- Cosgrove, Shaw, I just got
off the phone with dispatch.

05:54.437 --> 05:56.147
He didn’t make it
to the next station.

05:56.189 --> 05:59.029
- He’s got to still
be in here somewhere.

06:04.656 --> 06:05.906
- That gate should be locked.

06:05.949 --> 06:07.949
- He didn’t just stumble
on this gate.

06:07.993 --> 06:09.453
- Where the hell
did he get a key?

06:09.494 --> 06:11.294
- He must have
taken it off someone,

06:11.329 --> 06:13.289
a conductor or a worker.

06:13.331 --> 06:16.171
- That, or he is
a transit worker.

06:16.209 --> 06:19.169
[sirens wailing]

06:19.212 --> 06:26.392
♪

06:29.347 --> 06:31.677
- Where the hell did he go?

06:31.725 --> 06:33.560
- Back into the melting pot.

06:33.560 --> 06:44.279
.

06:44.279 --> 06:47.279
- Hey, Lieutenant.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.994
I think I found something.

06:49.034 --> 06:51.494
Cameras picked up a man,
masked, wearing a gray hoodie,

06:51.536 --> 06:54.406
carrying a camouflage bag
over by Canal Street.

06:54.456 --> 06:55.536
- Do we know where he goes?

06:55.582 --> 06:57.002
- Northbound on Baxter.

06:57.042 --> 06:59.172
And here on the northeast
corner of Columbus Park,

06:59.210 --> 07:01.880
he removes his sweatshirt,
tosses it in a trash can.

07:01.922 --> 07:02.922
- Call CSU right away.

07:02.964 --> 07:04.674
- I already did.
- Did they find it?

07:04.716 --> 07:07.546
- It’s on its way to the lab
for DNA analysis.

07:07.594 --> 07:09.304
20 minutes later,
cameras picked him up

07:09.346 --> 07:11.256
on Front Street.

07:11.306 --> 07:15.176
And this is definitely
the same bag.

07:15.226 --> 07:16.516
- It means he’s headed
toward the docks,

07:16.561 --> 07:18.191
probably trying
to board a ferry.

07:18.229 --> 07:20.019
- That’s what I thought,
but then watch.

07:20.065 --> 07:22.985
He turns right on Fletcher.
That’s where I lose him.

07:23.026 --> 07:25.566
- I used to walk a beat
in that neighborhood.

07:25.612 --> 07:28.412
I’m pretty sure
I know where he went.

07:30.742 --> 07:32.082
- This is
a person of interest.

07:32.118 --> 07:34.328
He was involved in
a subway shooting this morning.

07:34.371 --> 07:35.961
- I can’t really see his face.

07:35.997 --> 07:38.997
- But maybe you recognize
the body type or the gym bag.

07:39.042 --> 07:40.132
One of the straps is broken.

07:40.168 --> 07:41.248
- We think
he might have come in here,

07:41.294 --> 07:42.344
possibly to buy a weapon--

07:42.379 --> 07:43.959
a gun, a knife, a machete.

07:44.005 --> 07:45.795
- Maybe he’s looking
to buy some ammo.

07:45.840 --> 07:47.720
- Well, I don’t know
if it’s the same guy,

07:47.759 --> 07:50.299
but somebody did come in
with a green gym bag.

07:50.345 --> 07:52.015
Only they weren’t looking
to buy ammo.

07:52.055 --> 07:53.065
They were looking to sell it.

07:53.098 --> 07:54.768
- He sold you his ammunition?

07:54.808 --> 07:55.848
- No, he tried.

07:55.892 --> 07:57.892
- What caliber?
- 9-millimeter.

07:57.936 --> 08:00.056
Said he had 50 boxes.
Told him take a hike.

08:00.105 --> 08:01.315
- Are you sure about that?

08:01.356 --> 08:02.566
’Cause now would be the time
to come clean.

08:02.607 --> 08:04.067
- I run a legit shop.

08:04.109 --> 08:06.359
I’m not out there
buying ammo off the street.

08:06.403 --> 08:07.743
- All right.
Good to know.

08:07.779 --> 08:09.279
So you don’t mind
if we look around?

08:09.322 --> 08:10.952
- Be my guest.

08:10.991 --> 08:13.241
- Hey, buddy.
Can we ask you some questions?

08:13.284 --> 08:14.994
Hey, where are you going?

08:15.036 --> 08:16.496
- I don’t know anything.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.658
- Oh, ’cause we haven’t
asked you a question yet, so...

08:18.707 --> 08:21.747
- I meant I didn’t see that guy
you were just talking about.

08:21.793 --> 08:23.383
- You realize
the guy you didn’t see,

08:23.420 --> 08:24.380
the one that we’re looking for,

08:24.421 --> 08:25.921
shot up a subway this morning,

08:25.964 --> 08:27.224
killed seven people?

08:27.257 --> 08:29.377
- Yes, I do.

08:29.426 --> 08:31.086
- You interact with him?

08:31.136 --> 08:33.096
Yes or no?

08:33.138 --> 08:34.468
- I didn’t know who he was.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.604
I swear to God,
I was just looking

08:36.641 --> 08:38.601
to make a quick score,
you know?

08:38.643 --> 08:41.353
Ammo’s been selling
at a premium these days.

08:41.396 --> 08:43.016
He was offering
to sell it real cheap.

08:43.064 --> 08:44.984
- So you bought it off him.
That’s what you’re saying.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.735
- Not yet.

08:46.776 --> 08:48.896
I was gonna do it
on my lunch break.

08:48.945 --> 08:51.025
[tense music]

08:51.072 --> 08:58.002
♪

09:02.333 --> 09:04.293
- Is that our guy?

09:04.335 --> 09:06.085
- Definitely the same bag.

09:09.674 --> 09:12.344
- NYPD, don’t move!

09:12.385 --> 09:15.175
- [grunting]

09:15.221 --> 09:21.481
♪

09:25.273 --> 09:26.653
- Why did you make me run?

09:33.364 --> 09:35.454
- I got ammo,

09:35.492 --> 09:38.162
water bottles...

09:38.203 --> 09:39.453
trash.

09:39.496 --> 09:40.656
- Where are the guns?

09:40.705 --> 09:43.075
- Guns?
I don’t have any guns.

09:45.210 --> 09:46.380
- Picture of a little girl.

09:48.213 --> 09:49.593
Who’s this girl?

09:49.631 --> 09:51.471
- How the hell do I know?
- What’s this girl’s name?

09:51.508 --> 09:52.468
- I’m telling you,
I don’t know.

09:52.509 --> 09:54.469
It’s not my bag.

10:00.058 --> 10:01.768
I told you
I didn’t shoot anyone.

10:01.810 --> 10:03.690
I don’t even have a gun.
- So you just happened to be

10:03.728 --> 10:06.978
walking around lower Manhattan
with 50 boxes of live ammo

10:07.023 --> 10:08.863
a few hours
after a subway massacre?

10:08.900 --> 10:10.570
- Man, do yourself a favor
and tell us

10:10.610 --> 10:12.740
exactly
where you found that gym bag.

10:12.779 --> 10:14.359
- I found it on the street.
It was just laying there.

10:14.405 --> 10:15.485
- Where?
What street, Aaron?

10:15.532 --> 10:17.202
- Maybe there’s something
I could sell.

10:17.242 --> 10:19.492
I got a drug problem.
- Answer his question.

10:19.536 --> 10:21.496
Where exactly
did you find the gym bag?

10:21.538 --> 10:22.748
- In a dumpster.
- A dumpster?

10:22.789 --> 10:23.829
- I don’t know
the name of the street.

10:23.873 --> 10:25.043
- OK,
here’s what’s gonna happen.

10:25.083 --> 10:26.133
Take a look at this map.
You’re gonna tell me

10:26.167 --> 10:27.497
exactly
where you were this morning.

10:32.257 --> 10:33.837
- Rossi’s story checks out.

10:33.883 --> 10:37.223
There’s the racist son
of a bitch dumping the gym bag,

10:37.262 --> 10:39.682
and here’s Aaron Rossi
picking up the bag.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.349
- Facial recognition
give you anything?

10:44.394 --> 10:46.194
- He never took off the mask.

10:46.229 --> 10:47.609
- Great, so we’re nowhere.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.732
- How are you holding up,
Violet?

10:51.776 --> 10:53.896
- I’m just sick
of all the hate.

10:54.988 --> 10:56.278
- I get it.

10:56.322 --> 10:58.822
- Hey, I found eight schools
in the neighborhood

10:58.867 --> 11:00.197
that use that uniform
the little girl

11:00.243 --> 11:03.043
in the photo was wearing,
so let’s find her fast.

11:03.079 --> 11:04.709
Before he does.

11:09.544 --> 11:11.214
- Hi, Lacey.
I’m Kate.

11:11.254 --> 11:12.764
- She can’t hear you.

11:12.797 --> 11:15.717
- Oh, well, did we call
for an interpreter?

11:15.758 --> 11:17.638
- Yes, we did.
- Great.

11:17.677 --> 11:18.967
Do you prefer to sign?

11:20.138 --> 11:21.968
Yeah.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.775
Your mom, she’s gonna
be here soon, sweetie.

11:24.809 --> 11:29.559
But I just need to ask you
a few questions, OK?

11:29.606 --> 11:30.976
This picture.

11:31.024 --> 11:35.284
Does that man
look familiar to you?

11:35.320 --> 11:38.450
I know that the picture
is really blurry,

11:38.489 --> 11:41.699
but this is really important.

11:41.743 --> 11:44.753
Have you ever
seen that man before?

11:46.623 --> 11:47.833
[sighs]

11:50.627 --> 11:54.297
You know, your school,
the people there,

11:54.339 --> 11:56.219
they didn’t even know
your father’s name.

11:56.257 --> 11:58.717
Can you tell me his name?

11:58.760 --> 12:02.180
Can you tell me where he lives?

12:02.222 --> 12:04.142
Where he works?

12:04.182 --> 12:06.732
Can you tell me
what he looks like?

12:06.768 --> 12:09.148
His hair color?
Or is he tall?

12:09.187 --> 12:11.147
"You told me my mom
was gonna be here soon."

12:11.189 --> 12:12.229
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

12:12.273 --> 12:14.613
Your mom is--

12:14.651 --> 12:16.861
she’s on her way right now.

12:22.575 --> 12:24.285
- Where’s Lacey?
Where’s my daughter?

12:24.327 --> 12:25.327
- Hey, it’s OK.

12:25.370 --> 12:26.830
She’s fine.
She’s safe.

12:26.871 --> 12:27.831
She’s with the lieutenant.

12:27.872 --> 12:28.832
- What the hell happened?

12:28.873 --> 12:30.173
No one will tell me anything.

12:30.208 --> 12:31.748
- We’re investigating
the shooting that happened

12:31.793 --> 12:33.883
in the Canal Street Station
this morning.

12:33.920 --> 12:37.170
Your daughter’s photo was found
in the shooter’s gym bag.

12:38.967 --> 12:41.637
- What? Lacey’s photo
was in his gym bag?

12:41.678 --> 12:43.848
Why?
- We don’t know.

12:43.888 --> 12:45.678
Hoping you can help us
with that.

12:47.392 --> 12:48.732
You recognize this man?

12:51.896 --> 12:54.056
- I can barely
see the guy’s face.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.687
- Yeah, I get that, but is
there anything familiar at all?

13:00.405 --> 13:02.035
- I want a lawyer.

13:02.073 --> 13:04.373
- You’re entitled to one,
but this is not that.

13:04.409 --> 13:06.829
I’m just trying to figure out
what’s happening here, OK?

13:06.869 --> 13:10.249
Your daughter’s photo was
in the suspect’s gym bag.

13:10.290 --> 13:13.080
Do you know him?
- Like I said, I want a lawyer.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.376
- Lady, seven people
were killed this morning

13:15.420 --> 13:17.510
because of their race,
and you’re pulling this?

13:17.547 --> 13:19.467
- Lawyer.

13:19.507 --> 13:24.677
♪

13:24.721 --> 13:26.681
- What we know is
she’s married, one kid.

13:26.723 --> 13:28.223
No priors.

13:28.266 --> 13:29.426
- Husband?

13:29.475 --> 13:30.845
- Guy named Michael Farrell.

13:31.894 --> 13:33.064
- The girl is hungry.

13:33.104 --> 13:34.564
She wants pizza.

13:34.605 --> 13:35.555
Pepperoni.

13:35.606 --> 13:37.776
No, no, sausage.

13:37.817 --> 13:39.607
- How do you know how to--
- My son’s deaf.

13:39.652 --> 13:40.822
- Ah.

13:44.991 --> 13:47.201
- They’re both scared.

13:47.243 --> 13:50.163
She thinks her father could
be involved in the shooting.

13:50.204 --> 13:51.164
- Nah, I checked.

13:51.205 --> 13:52.405
Michael Farrell
is a metalworker.

13:52.457 --> 13:53.917
He’s been at the factory
since 7:30 this morning.

13:53.958 --> 13:56.338
He hasn’t left yet.

13:56.377 --> 13:58.587
- "Because we both know

13:58.629 --> 14:02.259
John is really, really mean."

14:02.300 --> 14:04.090
- John?
Who the hell is John?

14:04.135 --> 14:06.105
I thought the father’s name
was Michael.

14:06.137 --> 14:08.427
- Husband’s name is Michael.

14:08.473 --> 14:10.603
It doesn’t mean
it’s the girl’s father.

14:10.641 --> 14:17.690
♪

14:17.690 --> 14:26.240
.

14:26.240 --> 14:30.040
- DNA results are back
from the gray sweatshirt.

14:30.078 --> 14:31.248
Profile’s not in our system.

14:31.287 --> 14:32.537
- Do we have any idea

14:32.580 --> 14:34.580
why Jessica Farrell
is refusing to cooperate?

14:34.624 --> 14:36.174
- That’s
the million-dollar question.

14:36.209 --> 14:39.089
- We’d like to compel her to go
in front of the grand jury.

14:39.128 --> 14:40.628
Listen, that way,

14:40.671 --> 14:42.721
she might tell them
what she’s refusing to tell us.

14:42.757 --> 14:44.927
- If we go that route,
we have to immunize her.

14:44.967 --> 14:47.007
It could backfire.
- Got a better idea?

14:47.053 --> 14:48.973
- Not at the moment,
but I’m not excited

14:49.013 --> 14:51.473
about giving someone
a free pass on a mass shooting

14:51.516 --> 14:52.556
without more information.

14:52.600 --> 14:53.890
- The entire city
is at a standstill,

14:53.935 --> 14:57.315
waiting for us to get off
our asses to do our jobs.

14:57.355 --> 14:58.905
- What if he goes out
and kills again?

14:58.940 --> 15:00.770
You want that
on your conscience?

15:00.817 --> 15:02.437
- I don’t need a lecture,
Frank.

15:02.485 --> 15:05.285
I am fully aware
of what this man is capable of.

15:05.321 --> 15:07.741
- Well, her lawyer is
in interrogation room two.

15:07.782 --> 15:08.782
Why don’t you go in there
and see

15:08.825 --> 15:09.995
if you can work something out?

15:13.121 --> 15:14.661
- My client will cooperate,

15:14.705 --> 15:17.325
but she isn’t looking
for immunity.

15:17.375 --> 15:19.345
We’re not concerned
with criminal liability.

15:19.377 --> 15:21.837
- Then why won’t she talk?
- Fear.

15:21.879 --> 15:24.669
Your suspect is part
of a white supremacist group.

15:24.715 --> 15:26.675
- What if we put her
in Witness Protection?

15:26.717 --> 15:28.177
- She’s got a kid
and a sick parent.

15:28.219 --> 15:29.549
Can’t uproot her family.

15:29.595 --> 15:33.675
She wants to help,
but she needs some assurances.

15:33.724 --> 15:35.524
- She’ll give us his full name?
- Yes.

15:35.560 --> 15:36.980
- Can she lead us
to where he’s hiding?

15:37.019 --> 15:38.559
- She believes she can.

15:38.604 --> 15:42.904
- If Jessica Farrell gives a
complete and truthful statement

15:42.942 --> 15:45.692
and is not involved
in criminal activity,

15:45.736 --> 15:47.816
we’ll keep her identity
confidential.

15:47.864 --> 15:50.124
- No one will know
how you found him?

15:50.158 --> 15:51.738
- You have my word.

15:54.579 --> 15:56.039
- His name is John Nelson.

15:56.080 --> 15:57.710
We were together
for a couple of months.

15:57.748 --> 15:59.958
I got pregnant.
He split.

16:00.001 --> 16:01.041
- Date of birth?

16:01.085 --> 16:02.375
- He’s 32.

16:02.420 --> 16:04.210
His birthday’s in June.

16:04.255 --> 16:05.385
- Occupation?

16:05.423 --> 16:06.883
- He worked
for the Transit Authority

16:06.924 --> 16:08.514
up until a couple months ago.

16:08.551 --> 16:10.221
- You know
what he did with Transit?

16:10.261 --> 16:12.181
- He was, like, a mechanic.

16:12.221 --> 16:15.021
- Have you ever heard him
express anti-Asian bias?

16:16.726 --> 16:18.516
- He’s got this thing
against Asian people.

16:18.561 --> 16:20.401
It’s, like, totally crazy.

16:20.438 --> 16:22.358
He blames them for COVID.
- Hmm.

16:22.398 --> 16:24.728
- Started going up
to Asian people,

16:24.775 --> 16:26.395
telling them
they couldn’t get on the train.

16:26.444 --> 16:28.614
It’s why he got fired
from his job.

16:28.654 --> 16:30.914
- Are you aware
of any mental health issues?

16:30.948 --> 16:33.988
- Is being a mean, nasty son of
a bitch a mental health issue?

16:34.035 --> 16:35.705
- Do you know
where he is right now?

16:37.455 --> 16:39.335
- Look,
we can keep her out of it

16:39.373 --> 16:42.173
if she gives us all the
information she has right now.

16:46.464 --> 16:48.974
- I’ve been on his ass
for child support.

16:49.008 --> 16:51.428
Found out he’s been crashing
with a friend in Rockaway.

16:51.469 --> 16:53.549
- Have you been there recently?

16:54.639 --> 16:57.269
- I was there two days ago.

16:57.308 --> 17:00.768
- Do you believe that
he’s keeping his guns there?

17:00.811 --> 17:03.441
- It’s where
he keeps all his crap.

17:03.481 --> 17:05.441
[tense music]

17:05.483 --> 17:07.363
- NYPD!

17:07.401 --> 17:14.491
♪

17:19.163 --> 17:20.163
- Clear.

17:24.252 --> 17:25.542
- Clear.

17:27.255 --> 17:29.925
[clattering]

17:29.966 --> 17:31.626
- John.

17:31.676 --> 17:33.586
John, make this easy
on yourself.

17:35.346 --> 17:36.636
[gunshot]
- [groans]

17:36.681 --> 17:38.681
Shots fired.

17:38.724 --> 17:40.604
He’s going out the back.

17:44.021 --> 17:46.941
[sirens wailing]

17:48.776 --> 17:50.606
- Throw that!
Throw that gun!

17:50.653 --> 17:52.203
You drop that gun right now!

17:52.238 --> 17:54.108
- Don’t you get it, man?

17:54.156 --> 17:55.446
I’m doing you a favor.

17:55.491 --> 17:57.831
- Put the gun down!

17:57.868 --> 18:00.658
- These people are ruining
the country--our country!

18:00.705 --> 18:02.005
- You drop that gun right now,

18:02.039 --> 18:03.169
or I swear to God,
I’ll blow your head off.

18:03.207 --> 18:05.327
- They’re killing
innocent Americans, man!

18:05.376 --> 18:06.996
- Drop the gun now!

18:07.044 --> 18:09.054
- They need to be shipped back
to China, where they belong!

18:09.088 --> 18:12.128
[both grunting]

18:13.801 --> 18:16.511
- You are under arrest.

18:16.554 --> 18:18.224
- That means
you’re going to Rikers.

18:20.057 --> 18:22.137
Where you belong.

18:22.143 --> 18:29.233
.

18:29.233 --> 18:33.783
- Nelson was a no-show
at arraignment.

18:33.821 --> 18:36.241
I have no idea
where the hell he is.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.912
- The FBI pulled him
from the Tombs.

18:38.951 --> 18:41.291
- They just swooped in
and took him?

18:41.329 --> 18:43.459
- Hit him with a federal
detainer and hauled him off.

18:43.497 --> 18:46.627
The U.S. Attorney wants
to take over the prosecution.

18:46.667 --> 18:47.787
- What?
- I can’t say

18:47.835 --> 18:49.125
I appreciate their approach,

18:49.170 --> 18:51.960
but their interest in the case
is understandable.

18:52.006 --> 18:53.796
- That doesn’t mean--
- No, I agree.

18:53.841 --> 18:56.051
The NYPD
investigated this case.

18:56.093 --> 18:57.223
They put in the sweat.

18:57.261 --> 18:58.891
They consoled
the victims’ families.

18:58.929 --> 19:01.219
They took the heat
from the press.

19:01.265 --> 19:03.975
This happened in our city,
New York.

19:04.018 --> 19:06.478
Hell, I was there. I...

19:06.520 --> 19:08.810
I saw what this man did.

19:08.856 --> 19:10.566
No way
I’m letting this case go.

19:10.608 --> 19:12.028
- I’m on board,

19:12.068 --> 19:15.358
but there’s a few more people
you’ll need to convince.

19:23.120 --> 19:26.170
- You could have called,
Monica, given us a heads-up.

19:26.207 --> 19:27.417
- I apologize, Jack.

19:27.458 --> 19:29.208
I should have given you
fair warning,

19:29.251 --> 19:32.091
but Main Justice wants us
to take over the case.

19:32.129 --> 19:35.839
- I’m sure they do,
but this is a local crime.

19:35.883 --> 19:37.303
- Doesn’t mean
it’s not federal too.

19:37.343 --> 19:39.183
- Do you really want
to do this?

19:39.220 --> 19:41.180
Have a turf battle
over jurisdiction?

19:41.222 --> 19:43.972
Argue who’s best equipped
to try this case?

19:44.016 --> 19:45.846
- Like I said,

19:45.893 --> 19:49.563
Main Justice wants us
to take the lead.

19:52.900 --> 19:56.070
- I’d like to suggest
a compromise,

19:56.112 --> 19:58.572
something I think
we can both live with.

20:00.825 --> 20:03.165
It’s a little unconventional,
but it’s been done before.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.792
- How would it work?

20:04.829 --> 20:06.579
- You and Ms. Maroon
will be appointed

20:06.622 --> 20:09.542
special assistant
United States attorneys.

20:09.583 --> 20:11.173
- Who calls the shots?

20:11.210 --> 20:13.210
- You’ll be lead counsel.

20:13.254 --> 20:14.634
- They’ll agree to this?

20:14.672 --> 20:16.172
- Why not?

20:16.215 --> 20:17.755
If they win,
they get the credit.

20:17.800 --> 20:18.800
If they lose...

20:18.843 --> 20:20.683
- I shoulder the blame.

20:20.720 --> 20:21.850
- We.

20:21.887 --> 20:23.597
- Which means me.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.888
Yeah, let’s do it.

20:27.935 --> 20:29.595
- There’s a catch.

20:29.645 --> 20:31.435
The deal is predicated

20:31.480 --> 20:34.650
on your agreeing to ask
for the death penalty.

20:34.692 --> 20:37.652
[tense music]

20:37.695 --> 20:44.245
♪

20:44.285 --> 20:46.875
- I’m not sure I can set
my personal beliefs aside.

20:46.912 --> 20:51.122
- Your personal beliefs
are not part of the equation.

20:52.334 --> 20:53.924
If you don’t want
to go down that road,

20:53.961 --> 20:55.301
if you’re not willing

20:55.337 --> 20:58.587
to follow the federal statutes
and DOJ mandate,

20:58.632 --> 21:00.682
just say so.

21:00.718 --> 21:05.468
I’ll hand the damn case
back to the U.S. Attorney.

21:05.514 --> 21:12.444
♪

21:19.987 --> 21:21.317
- Andrea.

21:23.491 --> 21:25.951
How are you doing?
Haven’t seen you since--

21:25.993 --> 21:28.543
- Our law school reunion.

21:28.579 --> 21:31.289
Nolan and I volunteered for
the Innocence Project together.

21:31.332 --> 21:34.422
We used to fight like hell
to keep people off death row.

21:34.460 --> 21:35.630
Are you really doing this?

21:35.669 --> 21:37.379
You’re going
for the death penalty?

21:37.421 --> 21:39.381
- Under the law.
- The law?

21:39.423 --> 21:40.883
We’re talking
about the death penalty.

21:40.925 --> 21:42.475
- Next time,
tell your client

21:42.510 --> 21:45.720
not to kill
seven innocent Asian Americans.

21:45.763 --> 21:48.393
- Before you walk away
in a righteous huff,

21:48.432 --> 21:51.272
I’m gonna need the name
of your confidential informant.

21:54.396 --> 21:56.516
See what I mean
about that righteous huff?

21:59.026 --> 22:01.316
- It’s a simple
discovery request.

22:01.362 --> 22:03.282
- Simple but outrageous.

22:03.322 --> 22:04.702
The defense is asking us

22:04.740 --> 22:07.990
to disclose the identity
of our confidential informant.

22:08.035 --> 22:09.695
- I’ll hear you, Ms. Rankin.

22:09.745 --> 22:12.325
- The prosecution’s entire case
is built on a house of cards.

22:12.373 --> 22:14.373
Their so-called
"confidential informant"

22:14.416 --> 22:16.956
provided the information that
led to the defendant’s capture

22:17.002 --> 22:18.132
and the seizure of a gun.

22:18.170 --> 22:19.710
- The gun was analyzed

22:19.755 --> 22:21.295
and determined
to be the murder weapon.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.590
- And it was obtained
with a lawful search warrant.

22:23.634 --> 22:24.764
- Not necessarily.

22:24.802 --> 22:27.012
It could be fruit
of the poisonous tree.

22:27.054 --> 22:29.184
We have a right
to challenge the basis

22:29.223 --> 22:30.523
of the informant’s knowledge.

22:30.558 --> 22:31.978
We want to test
their credibility

22:32.017 --> 22:34.847
and assess whether or not
the information was reliable.

22:34.895 --> 22:37.305
Frankly, we don’t know
if this person even exists.

22:37.356 --> 22:38.896
- Your Honor,
that is a baseless

22:38.941 --> 22:40.861
and defamatory accusation.

22:40.901 --> 22:43.571
- It wouldn’t be the first time
NYPD made up an informant.

22:43.612 --> 22:46.032
- This is nothing more
than a thinly veiled attempt

22:46.073 --> 22:49.453
to intimidate our informant
and expose them to danger.

22:49.493 --> 22:51.413
The defendant is a killer.

22:51.453 --> 22:54.333
He’s part of a network
of white supremacists.

22:54.373 --> 22:57.673
- OK, not so simple.

22:57.710 --> 23:00.840
The defense has raised
a legitimate concern,

23:00.880 --> 23:03.720
and this is a capital case.

23:05.301 --> 23:08.551
I’m granting
the defendant’s motion.

23:08.596 --> 23:11.466
- You’re ordering me to reveal
the informant’s identity?

23:11.515 --> 23:15.305
- Disclose their name
or I’m dismissing the case.

23:15.352 --> 23:22.442
♪

23:22.443 --> 23:28.282
.

23:28.282 --> 23:31.082
- We promised Jessica
we’d protect her.

23:31.118 --> 23:34.248
We can’t just renege on that.

23:34.288 --> 23:35.958
- Judge doesn’t see it
that way, Nolan.

23:35.998 --> 23:37.458
- It’s a dangerous precedent,

23:37.499 --> 23:41.499
forcing confidential informants
to testify in open court,

23:41.545 --> 23:43.295
reveal their identity.

23:43.339 --> 23:44.629
It’s hard enough
to get witnesses

23:44.673 --> 23:45.923
to come forward these days.

23:45.966 --> 23:48.756
- You’re absolutely right,
but once again--

23:48.802 --> 23:51.682
- I know, I know.
The judge doesn’t care.

23:51.722 --> 23:55.352
So what do we do,
appeal the ruling?

23:55.392 --> 23:57.892
- We could, but we’ll lose.

24:00.356 --> 24:04.356
- So...just roll over?

24:04.401 --> 24:06.111
Throw Jessica to the wolves?

24:06.153 --> 24:07.703
- There is a way out.

24:09.615 --> 24:11.745
Offer Nelson a plea.

24:11.784 --> 24:13.454
- A plea?

24:13.494 --> 24:15.334
He killed seven people.

24:15.371 --> 24:17.121
- If we take the death penalty
off the table,

24:17.164 --> 24:18.504
maybe they’ll bite.

24:18.540 --> 24:20.130
Jessica doesn’t need
to testify,

24:20.167 --> 24:21.997
Nelson does life in prison,

24:22.044 --> 24:24.214
and you won’t have
to live with the fact--

24:24.254 --> 24:26.094
- No, no, no, no.
Don’t do that.

24:26.131 --> 24:27.381
- Excuse me?

24:29.093 --> 24:30.803
- This is not
about my beliefs

24:30.844 --> 24:34.894
or me having to live
with my choices.

24:34.932 --> 24:37.392
Jack made a deal
with the U.S. Attorney.

24:37.434 --> 24:38.694
We can’t walk that back.

24:38.727 --> 24:41.897
Like it or not,
under federal law,

24:41.939 --> 24:44.689
Nelson qualifies
for a death sentence.

24:46.610 --> 24:48.860
- Then Jessica Farrell
needs to testify.

24:52.866 --> 24:55.156
- You’re a liar.
- The judge left me no choice.

24:55.202 --> 24:56.412
- You promised.

24:56.453 --> 24:58.583
You said
no one would know my name.

24:58.622 --> 25:00.422
Now my face is
all over the Internet.

25:00.457 --> 25:01.787
And what about my daughter?

25:01.834 --> 25:03.634
She has to grow up
with everyone knowing

25:03.669 --> 25:05.339
her father is a racist killer?

25:05.379 --> 25:06.509
- I apologize.

25:06.547 --> 25:08.167
- We all want the same thing--

25:08.215 --> 25:09.795
to keep John Nelson
off the streets,

25:09.842 --> 25:10.972
to punish him for what he did.

25:12.511 --> 25:13.851
- I’m not gonna do it.

25:13.887 --> 25:17.807
- Unfortunately,
your testimony is mandatory.

25:17.850 --> 25:18.890
- I don’t care.

25:20.227 --> 25:21.937
- You’re under subpoena.

25:21.979 --> 25:23.939
If you don’t cooperate
voluntarily,

25:23.981 --> 25:25.271
you will be arrested.

25:25.315 --> 25:27.605
- I’ll be arrested?

25:27.651 --> 25:28.781
Is this some kind of joke?

25:28.819 --> 25:31.109
- I’m sorry,
but it’s the law.

25:31.155 --> 25:33.785
- It’s the law?

25:33.824 --> 25:38.454
That’s how you guys justify all
your lies and manipulations.

25:38.495 --> 25:40.825
You just blame it
on the damn law.

25:45.711 --> 25:48.091
- Ms. Farrell, could you
tell the members of the jury

25:48.130 --> 25:50.720
how you know the defendant?

25:52.593 --> 25:56.473
- I just do.
I don’t remember where we met.

25:56.513 --> 26:00.313
- Were you two
involved romantically?

26:00.350 --> 26:02.730
- Not how I’d describe it.

26:02.770 --> 26:04.310
- Do you have a child together?

26:04.354 --> 26:05.814
- Objection. Relevance.

26:05.856 --> 26:08.146
- I’m trying to establish
her basis of knowledge,

26:08.192 --> 26:09.652
her connection
to the defendant.

26:09.693 --> 26:10.993
- Can you leave my daughter
the hell out of this?

26:11.028 --> 26:13.148
- Let’s keep moving.

26:13.197 --> 26:14.407
- Your Honor,
I’d move to have

26:14.448 --> 26:16.828
Ms. Farrell declared
a hostile witness.

26:16.867 --> 26:18.577
- I believe you’ve laid
a proper foundation.

26:18.619 --> 26:20.249
You may proceed
with leading questions.

26:20.287 --> 26:21.497
- Thank you.
Did you meet

26:21.538 --> 26:23.158
with Detectives Cosgrove
and Shaw

26:23.207 --> 26:25.497
and tell them
where the defendant was living?

26:29.046 --> 26:31.456
- You told me
I’d never have to testify.

26:31.507 --> 26:32.587
- Your Honor,
may the witness be ordered

26:32.633 --> 26:33.973
to answer the question?

26:34.009 --> 26:35.799
- Ask another one.

26:40.265 --> 26:42.135
- You told detectives

26:42.184 --> 26:45.104
that Mr. Nelson was living
in Rockaway, didn’t you?

26:45.145 --> 26:46.725
- I don’t recall.

26:46.772 --> 26:48.652
- You told them
he was keeping weapons there.

26:48.690 --> 26:50.150
- I don’t remember saying that.

26:50.192 --> 26:51.692
- Your Honor, given
that the defendant’s arrest

26:51.735 --> 26:53.645
and the seizure
of the so-called murder weapon

26:53.695 --> 26:55.155
were predicated
on the information

26:55.197 --> 26:56.527
provided by this witness,

26:56.573 --> 26:58.373
I move to suppress the TEC-9.

27:00.077 --> 27:01.537
- Your motion is allowed.

27:01.578 --> 27:03.868
Members of the jury,
you’re not to consider

27:03.914 --> 27:05.964
any mention of the gun
being found

27:05.999 --> 27:09.539
in the house
where Mr. Nelson was living.

27:09.586 --> 27:13.256
[tense music]

27:13.298 --> 27:19.138
♪

27:22.266 --> 27:24.886
- You lost the murder weapon.

27:24.935 --> 27:27.315
- It was excluded, but
the jury isn’t gonna be able

27:27.354 --> 27:28.864
to wipe it
from their memory.

27:28.897 --> 27:30.567
- The U.S. Attorney called.

27:30.607 --> 27:33.987
They offered to send in
an AUSA to help.

27:34.027 --> 27:35.737
- I don’t need any help.

27:35.779 --> 27:38.069
- It might not look that way
to those watching the trial.

27:38.115 --> 27:41.875
- I have other evidence--
the video, the gym bag, motive.

27:43.787 --> 27:46.577
- You asked
for this case, Nolan.

27:46.623 --> 27:48.123
I went out on a limb,

27:48.167 --> 27:50.917
worked out a deal
so you could be lead counsel.

27:50.961 --> 27:53.761
If Nelson walks,
everyone in this city

27:53.797 --> 27:56.677
will lose faith in our ability
to serve and protect.

27:56.717 --> 28:00.047
- We’re good, Jack.

28:00.095 --> 28:01.345
You have my word.

28:01.388 --> 28:03.718
- I don’t care about your word.

28:06.393 --> 28:08.563
I care about the verdict.

28:14.318 --> 28:17.648
- Were you on the 6 Train
at the Canal Street Station

28:17.696 --> 28:19.816
on August 16?

28:19.865 --> 28:21.625
- Yes.

28:21.658 --> 28:24.788
- Can you tell us
what happened?

28:24.828 --> 28:28.748
- I was on my phone,
doing the Wordle,

28:28.790 --> 28:32.540
when all of a sudden,
I heard these loud noises.

28:33.712 --> 28:35.802
At first,
I didn’t know what it was.

28:35.839 --> 28:37.259
- They were gunshots?

28:38.592 --> 28:40.052
- Dozens.

28:42.596 --> 28:44.806
People started falling
to the ground,

28:44.848 --> 28:48.138
diving under their seats.

28:48.185 --> 28:49.145
Some of us got hit.

28:50.854 --> 28:53.654
- Were you struck
by the gunfire?

28:53.690 --> 28:56.150
- In my leg.

28:56.193 --> 28:58.533
I’d probably be dead
if it wasn’t for you.

29:01.281 --> 29:04.781
- Please tell
the members of the jury

29:04.826 --> 29:09.246
what happened
after you were shot.

29:09.289 --> 29:11.119
- I fell to the ground.

29:13.377 --> 29:17.127
I just remember looking
at the filthy floor.

29:18.882 --> 29:23.512
And I saw a pool
of blood forming,

29:23.553 --> 29:26.683
and I realized it was my blood.

29:28.725 --> 29:33.645
He was moving up the train
like he was hunting us.

29:36.149 --> 29:38.899
I closed my eyes, and...

29:38.944 --> 29:41.034
I pretended I was dead.

29:44.491 --> 29:45.741
The train pulled
into the station,

29:45.784 --> 29:47.664
and he stopped shooting.

29:49.496 --> 29:53.246
The doors opened,
and everybody ran out.

29:55.168 --> 29:59.668
People were screaming
and pushing.

30:01.925 --> 30:05.385
Somehow, I managed to drag
myself onto the platform.

30:05.429 --> 30:08.719
- Do you believe you were
targeted because of your race?

30:08.765 --> 30:10.475
- Objection. Relevance.

30:10.517 --> 30:11.887
- Overruled.

30:11.935 --> 30:14.225
The witness may answer.

30:14.271 --> 30:21.401
♪

30:22.195 --> 30:25.905
- He aimed his gun
at the Asian people.

30:25.949 --> 30:29.039
He moved past people
who looked white,

30:29.077 --> 30:31.867
and he shot at anybody
who appeared to be Asian.

30:35.834 --> 30:38.504
This is what it’s like
to live in America these days.

30:38.545 --> 30:40.085
- What do you mean by that?

30:40.130 --> 30:42.880
- I was born in this country.

30:42.924 --> 30:44.224
Not that it should matter,

30:44.259 --> 30:48.889
but I’ve lived here
my entire life.

30:48.930 --> 30:51.470
And I’ve seen hostility before,

30:51.516 --> 30:55.186
but not like this.

30:55.228 --> 30:57.438
COVID and the lies

30:57.481 --> 30:59.521
that are being perpetuated
about its origins,

30:59.566 --> 31:02.896
it’s unleashed a hate
like I have never seen before.

31:04.988 --> 31:07.068
Every time
I leave my apartment,

31:07.115 --> 31:10.945
I worry that someone might bash
me over the head with a rock

31:10.994 --> 31:13.914
because of how I look.

31:13.955 --> 31:15.535
My parents are afraid.

31:15.582 --> 31:18.002
My--my grandmother...

31:21.129 --> 31:24.759
- Do you see the man who shot
you in this courtroom today?

31:27.594 --> 31:33.394
- I can’t be 100% certain
because I didn’t see his face,

31:33.433 --> 31:34.933
but he looks like him--

31:34.976 --> 31:38.766
his height,
his weight,

31:38.814 --> 31:40.824
his eyes.

31:40.857 --> 31:42.357
- May the record reflect

31:42.401 --> 31:46.451
that the witness indicated
the defendant, John Nelson.

31:46.488 --> 31:49.988
- The record shall so reflect.

31:50.033 --> 31:52.743
- Thank you.
Nothing further.

31:54.329 --> 31:56.789
- Cross-examination?

31:56.832 --> 31:58.542
- The defense has no questions.

31:58.583 --> 32:02.843
In fact, we stipulate
that this was a hate crime.

32:09.553 --> 32:12.013
- Why would she agree
that this was a hate crime?

32:12.055 --> 32:14.555
- Well, it makes our lives
a hell of a lot easier, though.

32:14.599 --> 32:16.179
- Yeah, rolling over

32:16.226 --> 32:18.766
and agreeing to a crucial
element of the offense

32:18.812 --> 32:20.812
is not Andrea’s style.
[phone buzzes]

32:22.649 --> 32:24.609
- Well...
- What?

32:24.651 --> 32:26.031
- You’re right.

32:26.069 --> 32:27.359
She’s agreed
to the hate crime theory

32:27.404 --> 32:29.284
because she wants
to use it against us.

32:29.322 --> 32:31.032
- How?
- They’re changing their plea

32:31.074 --> 32:33.124
to not guilty
by reason of insanity,

32:33.160 --> 32:36.870
claiming pathological bigotry
is a mental disease or defect.

32:36.913 --> 32:40.041
♪

32:40.041 --> 32:46.298
.

32:46.298 --> 32:49.468
- Mr. Nelson blames
Asian Americans

32:49.509 --> 32:51.719
for the spread of COVID,
for the pandemic,

32:51.761 --> 32:55.391
for pretty much
everything that followed.

32:55.432 --> 32:59.942
- So he blames people who have
never stepped foot in Asia

32:59.978 --> 33:01.938
for all of that?

33:01.980 --> 33:05.230
- His thought process
is not rational.

33:05.275 --> 33:07.825
- Dr. Thibodeau,
do you believe him

33:07.861 --> 33:11.571
to be suffering from
a mental disease or illness?

33:11.615 --> 33:12.745
- I do.

33:12.782 --> 33:14.702
- And
in your professional opinion,

33:14.743 --> 33:18.253
was he able to distinguish
between fact and fiction

33:18.288 --> 33:19.958
on the day of the murders?

33:19.998 --> 33:23.838
- I believe he was unable
to understand

33:23.877 --> 33:26.747
the wrongful nature
of his acts.

33:26.796 --> 33:28.006
- Thank you.

33:31.510 --> 33:36.220
- The defendant was organized
and rational enough

33:36.264 --> 33:38.854
to figure out how to purchase
an assault weapon.

33:38.892 --> 33:42.852
And he knew how to fill out
the requisite paperwork,

33:42.896 --> 33:46.766
how to find a store that sold
the type of weapon required

33:46.816 --> 33:50.106
to carry out such a massive
and destructive assault.

33:50.153 --> 33:51.613
- Doesn’t mean he’s sane.
- He figured out

33:51.655 --> 33:54.995
how to obtain the ammunition,
load the gun,

33:55.033 --> 33:57.123
hide it in a gym bag.
- I suppose.

33:57.160 --> 33:58.490
- Got himself to an area

33:58.537 --> 34:01.657
that has a disproportionately
high concentration

34:01.706 --> 34:03.286
of Asian Americans.

34:03.333 --> 34:06.133
- Again, doesn’t mean he wasn’t
suffering from mental illness.

34:06.169 --> 34:08.669
- No, it means he was
able to think clearly.

34:08.713 --> 34:11.473
He was also able
to figure out an escape route.

34:11.508 --> 34:13.628
- Yes.
- He even brought a key

34:13.677 --> 34:16.467
with him so he could
unlock a gate in the tunnel.

34:16.513 --> 34:18.853
- Yes, but--
- You answered my question.

34:18.890 --> 34:20.430
Nothing further.

34:20.475 --> 34:22.265
- Mr. Price just cut you off,

34:22.310 --> 34:24.770
but I would like to hear
the rest of your answer.

34:24.813 --> 34:27.773
- I was going to say,
in my expert opinion,

34:27.816 --> 34:29.566
Mr. Nelson’s pathologic desire

34:29.609 --> 34:32.069
to eliminate
an entire race of people

34:32.112 --> 34:34.362
would qualify
as a delusional disorder.

34:34.406 --> 34:37.776
I further believe that
his extreme racist beliefs

34:37.826 --> 34:39.906
are evidence of psychosis.

34:39.953 --> 34:42.583
- So what you’re saying is

34:42.622 --> 34:46.752
my client may be
a despicable human being,

34:46.793 --> 34:48.593
but he’s still a human being...
- Objection.

34:48.628 --> 34:51.878
- And sentencing
a mentally ill person to death

34:51.923 --> 34:53.303
is nothing short of barbaric?

34:53.341 --> 34:54.471
- Your Honor, objection.

34:54.509 --> 34:57.099
- Withdrawn.
Nothing further.

35:07.355 --> 35:09.645
Are you really trying
to execute my client?

35:09.691 --> 35:11.191
- Please, Andrea,
don’t do this.

35:11.234 --> 35:13.194
- Do what?
- This.

35:15.572 --> 35:17.322
- I was feeling nostalgic
last night,

35:17.365 --> 35:19.655
so I pulled out
an old law review article.

35:19.701 --> 35:22.791
The first sentence
went something like this:

35:22.829 --> 35:27.079
"Capital punishment
is barbaric in theory,

35:27.125 --> 35:29.035
"indiscriminate in practice,

35:29.085 --> 35:32.955
"and an intolerable denial of
the fundamental civil liberties

35:33.006 --> 35:35.126
guaranteed
under the Constitution."

35:37.385 --> 35:39.465
You wrote that, Nolan.

35:39.512 --> 35:40.972
You did.

35:41.014 --> 35:45.564
And now you’re trying to put
a mentally ill man to death.

35:49.272 --> 35:51.732
- This isn’t about me

35:51.775 --> 35:55.325
or about some article
that I wrote 20 years ago.

35:55.362 --> 35:57.912
It’s about the law.

35:57.947 --> 36:00.237
- No, that’s a cop-out.

36:00.283 --> 36:03.413
You are choosing to do this.

36:03.453 --> 36:05.413
Don’t ask me why,
but you are.

36:05.455 --> 36:08.375
[tense music]

36:08.416 --> 36:15.376
♪

36:20.011 --> 36:24.351
- I hear the psychiatrist
was pretty effective.

36:24.391 --> 36:25.771
- I wouldn’t go that far,

36:25.809 --> 36:29.769
but Rankin knows
how to put on a show.

36:29.813 --> 36:32.273
A few of the jurors
seemed intrigued.

36:32.315 --> 36:34.315
- You need to put on a show
of your own.

36:34.359 --> 36:37.739
Bring home who this man,
Nelson, really is,

36:37.779 --> 36:42.239
that his decisions were those
of a lucid, hateful monster.

36:42.283 --> 36:45.663
Is there another witness
you can call,

36:45.704 --> 36:48.214
perhaps an exhibit
or a piece of evidence

36:48.248 --> 36:50.708
that can bring them back
to the scene?

36:56.089 --> 36:58.759
- I think I can do one better.

36:58.800 --> 37:05.390
♪

37:06.850 --> 37:09.480
You saw his escape route.

37:09.519 --> 37:13.519
Now please take note

37:13.565 --> 37:17.825
of where the victims
were situated.

37:17.861 --> 37:20.321
You heard
that the train was packed--

37:20.363 --> 37:22.533
a variety
of ethnicities and races--

37:22.574 --> 37:25.994
and yet,
he was able to locate

37:26.035 --> 37:30.665
and gun down
those who appeared to be Asian.

37:30.707 --> 37:33.827
Kimmi Hsu testified
that she was over here

37:33.877 --> 37:35.707
when a bullet
struck her in the leg.

37:40.049 --> 37:42.009
Nicked her femoral artery.

37:42.051 --> 37:44.511
Almost ended her life.

37:46.097 --> 37:49.677
And you heard evidence

37:49.726 --> 37:53.846
that 12-year-old Jimmy Park

37:53.897 --> 37:56.647
died right here,

37:56.691 --> 37:59.691
clutching his baseball mitt,

37:59.736 --> 38:03.816
after a bullet pierced
his lung, lodged in his heart.

38:03.865 --> 38:06.035
Jimmy’s
72-year-old grandmother,

38:06.075 --> 38:07.365
Heejin,
died first.

38:07.410 --> 38:11.960
She was sitting on that bench,
right there...

38:15.126 --> 38:19.586
When three bullets hit her
in the head and chest.

38:21.090 --> 38:23.760
According to Jimmy’s father,

38:23.802 --> 38:27.142
they were on their way
to Yankee Stadium.

38:27.180 --> 38:32.350
Consider the planning
and the concentration

38:32.393 --> 38:34.943
that went
into this horrific crime,

38:34.979 --> 38:38.729
the decisions and the choices
the defendant made

38:38.775 --> 38:42.905
in order to carry out
this despicable act.

38:42.946 --> 38:44.736
If John Nelson
was really suffering

38:44.781 --> 38:48.701
from the acute mental illness
that Dr. Thibodeau described,

38:48.743 --> 38:51.373
there is no way in hell

38:51.412 --> 38:55.002
he’d ever have been able
to pull off a crime...

38:56.584 --> 38:59.674
A crime of this magnitude.

39:04.092 --> 39:06.802
We’d all like

39:06.845 --> 39:10.515
to make sense of what happened,

39:10.557 --> 39:12.347
chalk it up to mental illness,

39:12.392 --> 39:14.942
but the hard truth

39:14.978 --> 39:19.768
is that some people
are just evil.

39:21.818 --> 39:26.318
John Nelson opened fire
in that subway

39:26.364 --> 39:30.334
because he is a hateful,

39:30.368 --> 39:34.458
rage-filled,

39:34.497 --> 39:37.417
evil man.

39:37.458 --> 39:44.008
♪

39:51.014 --> 39:53.024
- Nolan?

39:53.057 --> 39:54.477
Nolan?

39:54.517 --> 39:57.557
Hey, you good?

39:59.230 --> 40:00.770
Jury’s back.

40:04.777 --> 40:09.027
- Fiat iustitia,
et pereat mundus.

40:09.073 --> 40:12.743
May justice be done,
though the world perish.

40:16.289 --> 40:17.829
- Mr. Foreman,

40:17.874 --> 40:20.174
having previously
found the defendant guilty

40:20.209 --> 40:21.669
of seven counts of murder,

40:21.711 --> 40:23.801
have you agreed
upon a sentence?

40:23.838 --> 40:24.668
- We have.

40:24.714 --> 40:27.014
- What say you?

40:27.050 --> 40:30.470
- We sentence the defendant,
John Nelson,

40:30.511 --> 40:33.351
to death by lethal injection.

40:33.389 --> 40:40.559
♪

40:49.781 --> 40:52.661
- Join me for a drink?
- Rain check.

40:56.913 --> 40:58.253
Andrea?

40:58.289 --> 41:00.369
Hey, you did a nice job.

41:00.416 --> 41:03.206
- I can’t believe you actually
went through with it.

41:03.252 --> 41:06.012
You sent a man to his death.

41:06.047 --> 41:09.127
- I did my job,
just like you.

41:11.260 --> 41:13.300
- You’ve changed, Nolan.

41:13.346 --> 41:20.056
♪

41:20.061 --> 41:26.025
.

41:26.025 --> 41:28.735
[dramatic music]

41:28.778 --> 41:35.698
♪

41:55.096 --> 41:57.966
[wolf howls]
